<%- include('../partials/header') %>
    <div class="static-page">
        <h1>About Alexandria</h1>
        <div class="prose">
            <p>Alexandria is an independent journal dedicated to rigorous analysis and thoughtful discourse across the humanities and social sciences. We publish both long-form essays and shorter analytical pieces spanning five core disciplines: history, politics, law, economics, and philosophy.</p>
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>We believe that careful, evidence-based analysis has the power to illuminate complex issues and foster meaningful dialogue. In an era of information overload and surface-level commentary, Alexandria offers a space for depth, nuance, and intellectual rigour.</p>
            <h2>Editorial Standards</h2>
            <p>Every piece published in Alexandria undergoes editorial review. We are committed to accuracy, fairness, and transparency. When errors occur, we issue corrections promptly. In rare cases where the integrity of a published piece is fundamentally compromised, we issue formal retractions while keeping the original text accessible for the record.</p>
            <h2>Contributing</h2>
            <p>We welcome submissions from scholars, practitioners, and thoughtful commentators working across our five disciplines. If you have an idea for an article, please reach out through our contact page with a brief outline and your background.</p>
            <h2>Editorial Team</h2>
            <p>Alexandria is edited by a distributed team of section editors and copy editors. This section is where we feature the people shaping every issue.</p>
            <div class="editorial-grid">
                <article class="editor-card">
                    <h3>Editor-in-Chief</h3>
                    <p>Leads the editorial line and approves final publication decisions.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="editor-card">
                    <h3>History &amp; Politics Editors</h3>
                    <p>Develop long-form essays, source checks, and fact-grounded analysis.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="editor-card">
                    <h3>Law &amp; Economics Editors</h3>
                    <p>Oversee argument clarity, citations, and methodological consistency.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="editor-card">
                    <h3>Philosophy Editor</h3>
                    <p>Curates conceptual pieces and ensures logical rigor in debate writing.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="editor-card">
                    <h3>Copy &amp; Production Editors</h3>
                    <p>Polish style, manage schedules, and prepare stories for release.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
            <p>If you’d like your editor profile listed here, please contact us with your preferred name, role, and short bio.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
